<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 90-year-old woman was crushed and killed by a pickup truck while crossing the 
street Sunday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Adeline Belinda was crossing the street at 10th Avenue and B Street at 2:50 
p.m. when David Crouse, 32, of Coronado, drove his pickup truck through a red 
light and was broadsided by another vehicle, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Crouse's truck, which had been travelling westbound on B Street, rolled over 
and fell on Belinda, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Belinda was taken to UCSD Medical Center where she died at 6:45 p.m., hospital 
authorities said. 
