<HEADLINE>
<P>
RABBI KAHANE'S CONTRIBUTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is symptomatic of the leftist detractors of the Jewish people, many of whose 
vociferous exponents are unfortunately themselves Jewish, that they 
misunderstand the phenomenon of Rabbi Kahane. 
</P>
<P>
Sprinzak's assessment of Kahane's popular support is absolutely wrong. 
</P>
<P>
We know that this is true due to the fear of the so-called "right-wing" party 
and its collaboration with the leftists to attempt to liquidate Rabbi Kahane 
through parliamentary maneuvering. It is this "right-wing" that had the most to 
fear of the rabbi: a substantial loss of financial support and portfolios in 
government. His prophetic prediction of an emasculated Likud government, 
financially subservient to the largess of U.S., has been proven correct. This 
poses as a real danger to Israel. 
</P>
<P>
The truth that the leftists and their Arab supporters fail to see is that there 
cannot, nor will there be, any peaceful coexistence between Arabs and Jews in 
our land. 
</P>
<P>
The leftists and Jewish apologists refuse and abhor the concept of the 
revelation of Mt. Sinai, decreeing the exclusivity of the land of Israel to the 
Jewish people. What they mistakenly mistake for "neo-religious ideas about 
redemption" and the "indivisibility of the land of Israel" as undesirable are 
nothing more than a genuine, healthy Jewish reawakening of their identity as a 
people, a reacceptance of the yoke of G-d's kingdom. 
</P>
<P>
For those of us whose tears are not yet dried, the painful loss of Rabbi Kahane 
will only mean a redoubling of our efforts in the causes he dedicated his life 
for. 
</P>
<P>
RABBI NACHUM SHIFREN, Director, Center for Jewish Activism, Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
