<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Menudo Members Ousted on Pot Charges: Two singers with the pop teen band Menudo 
were arrested in Miami for possession of marijuana, then ousted from the group, 
which cultivates a clean-cut image. Police at Miami International Airport 
confiscated 45 grams of marijuana from Sergio Gonzalez, 18, and 38 grams from 
Ruben Gomez, 16, Thursday night as the group stopped in Miami en route to 
Venezuela from Mexico City. 
</P>
<P>
Both are free on bail after being charged with marijuana possession. The group, 
which has been active in anti-drug campaigns aimed at young teens, maintains 
its youthful appeal by rotating boys out of the group when they reach 16. 
Officials with Sonotone Music Corp., which distributes Menudo's albums, could 
not explain why 18-year-old Gonzalez was still in the group. CLAUDIA PUIG 
