BRUINS BEAT SOUTHERN METHODIST TO ADVANCE TO SOCCER SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IAN JAQUISS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Henderson scored an unassisted goal and Billy Thompson added another goal 
to send UCLA to college soccer's final four with a 2-0 victory over Southern 
Methodist in the NCAA West Regional title game Sunday at UCLA's North Field. 
</P>
<P>
The victory kept the Bruins unbeaten in their past 39 games at home and 
improved their record to 17-1-4. 
</P>
<P>
SMU finished at 18-4-1. 
</P>
