<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Big Advertiser Pulls Out: The New York Daily News, its circulation devastated 
by a month-long strike, has lost one of its biggest advertisers, Macy's 
department store, just as the heavy holiday advertising season is getting under 
way. 
</P>
<P>
Macy's confirmed that it has dropped its advertising in the Daily News. 
Officials at the striking unions said the A&amp;S department store, another big 
advertiser, has done the same. The newspaper's two tabloid rivals, the New York 
Post and New York Newsday, have reported large advertising and circulation 
gains since the sometimes-violent strike began Oct. 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
