<P>
Philips Halts Picture Tube Plant: A unit of Dutch-based NV Philips, the giant 
consumer electronics firm, has postponed plans for a $116-million picture tube 
plant in Saline, Mich., blaming a sluggish U.S. economy. Philips, which is 
based in Eindhoven, the Netherlands, recently announced that it lost $1.3 
billion in the third quarter and would lay off up to 45,000 of its 285,700 
employees worldwide. The company had planned to build the picture tube plant on 
117 acres and employ up to 400 people. 
