</P>
<P>
MIDWAY AIRLINES DELAYS SALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Midway Airlines Inc. said today that it agreed to delay closing on the planned 
sale of its Philadelphia operations to archrival USAir Group Inc. to give the 
Justice Department more time to review the deal. 
</P>
<P>
Chicago-based Midway announced in October that it would sell its costly 
Philadelphia expansion to USAir, the nation's seventh-biggest carrier, for 
$64.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
"We initially had indicated we thought the transaction would be completed 
before the first of December. . . . It now appears it will take a little 
longer," a Midway spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The deal was expected to face tough antitrust scrutiny since it would give 
USAir, already the largest operator in Philadelphia, more landing slots, 
authority for routes to Toronto and Montreal, 11 gates and other facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
